   <titleInfo>
      <title>The Nation's Investment in Children: An Analysis of the President's FY 1992 Budget Proposals</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <location>
      <physicalLocation valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2017113530">Langston Hughes Library (Children's Defense Fund Haley Farm)</physicalLocation>
   </location>
   <abstract>This report contains detailed information about the Bush Administration's FY 1992 Budget that affected 12.6 million poor children in our country. Infant mortality rates, homeless children and families, the foster care system, and failing schools are some of the areas covered in the report. Charts and graphs are used throughout the report to highlight the inadequate budget allocations that resulted in little to no improvement to the condition of poor children and families in the US.</abstract>
